      "description": "Presenting an investment-grade 2004 BMW M3 (E46) Coupe, finished in a concours-level aesthetic. This specimen is powered by the iconic S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and an 8,000 RPM redline. Power is delivered to the rear wheels via a crisp Getrag 6-speed manual gearbox and a factory-calibrated limited-slip differential. This vehicle has undergone comprehensive preventative maintenance: the VANOS unit has been overhauled, and the rear subframe has been professionally reinforced to exceed factory specifications. The suspension geometry remains true, with all bushings and dampers providing the communicative feedback synonymous with the M-division. With zero oxidation on the undercarriage and an interior devoid of bolster wear, this is a mechanically superior example for the discerning collector.",
